wiki.content: "Yo x Ti, Tu x Mí" is about an intense bond between two people who are willing to do anything for each other. Throughout the song, the singers repeatedly express their commitment to each other. They talk about going worldwide together, being in love, and having an unbreakable connection. In the first verse, Rosalía sings about how much she values the relationship and how committed she is. She talks about betting on the number seven and asking the other person to catch her should she fall. In the second verse, Ozuna contributes to the theme of the song by discussing how different this relationship is from anything he has ever experienced before. He talks about how lucky he is to have this connection and how strongly he feels about the other person. The chorus of the song, which repeats throughout, is a celebration of their bond. They repeatedly assert their willingness to do whatever is necessary for each other, even if it means being restrained by "grilletes", or handcuffs. Overall, "Yo x Ti, Tu x Mí" is a tribute to the power of love and loyalty in a relationship. The song is a moving declaration of commitment that reflects the passion that can exist between two people who truly love and support each other. Read more on Last.fm.
